So someone who comes under the effect of the SCP will struggle to retain eye contact, and will try to re-establish eye contact if it's broken?
附加记录：    

That was my intent. L. was only able to because he was doggedly persistent about resisting it.



Can someone actually survive for two days near the summit in a sleeping bag?
附加记录：    

L. is based on the real-life Lincoln Hall, who did indeed survive over 24 hours near the summit in a sleeping bag. Two days might be pushing the limits of possibility, but not quite impossible.



 doesn't seem to me like the sort of thing that would go into a dry report by the Foundation.
附加记录：    

I borrowed that line directly from the Wikipedia article on Hall. Cheerfully withdrawn.



This makes it sound like he became afraid of mountains because he remembered the encounter. Did the Foundation not dose him with amnesiacs?
附加记录：    

He would indeed have been dosed, but like the real Hall retired because of the physical trauma he suffered.







